reviews.headline: allergic reaction
reviews.comments: I've been using it for a couple of weeks and I've had an allergic reaction to it. I have sensitive skin and it's the only thing I've changed so I know it's this product.

reviews.headline: Collagen bank
reviews.comments: Non-greasy and SPF make this a plus for me.  That and it makes a good makeup primer. Haven't used it long enough to know if it's building more collagen.

reviews.headline: Great product, SPF seems to hold up
reviews.comments: I'll be purchasing again for sure. Even though the science is against collagen's skin permeability when applied topically, I really do feel like this makes my skin look nice and hydrated. Not greasy, rubs in easily. I used it as my only SPF on my face at the beach for a few hours without a base tan and didn't burn, despite being super fair. I have sensitive skin and it doesn't seem to break me out. I'd caution about getting it too close to your eyes, but that's the only downside.

reviews.headline: Pills
reviews.comments: This is a good one if not wearing other products. But it pills on top of other skincare/serums and under makeup. Will keep looking.

reviews.headline: Love this
reviews.comments: Oh my skin looks and feels so smooth and hydrated and plump. My make-up goes smooth over my skin.

reviews.headline: I wanted to love this but…
reviews.comments: Im so upset that i dont like this but it isnt good. I have combination skin and this made my skin SOOO dry. It feels like i have a mask on and its cracking. Dont know how else to describe it.

reviews.headline: I love this moisturizer!!!
reviews.comments: My skin was looking so dry and dull.. immediately after using my skin is so bright im literally glowing.. after a week my skin looks 1000% better. Definitely in my daily skin care!! I recommend this to anyone who will listen.

reviews.headline: Best Neutrogena Sunscreen
reviews.comments: This is the first Neutrogena sunscreen ive found that doesnt have a strong fragrance, dries down softly and doesnt look shiny on the skin. Bonus is doesnt burn around the eyes like many chemical sunscreens can. Only wish it were waterproof!

reviews.headline: Love the lightweight feel!
reviews.comments: Absolutely love how lightweight this SPF is - it feels amazing even when I apply it multiple times a day. Also makes me feel good that its helping preserve my collagen, to keep my skin youthful.

reviews.headline: Surprisingly nice!
reviews.comments: This feels like nothing on my skin, I'm a big fan!

reviews.headline: Neutrogena out did themselves
reviews.comments: This works amazing, I have the collagen bank without SPF in it. Just started using and I have no complaints. Love that I can use this as my daily sunscreen and help my skin

reviews.headline: Great for my sensitive acne prone skin
reviews.comments: I have acne prone skin and have been searching for a good sunscreen. This one seems to work and hasnt broke me out. I'd say give it a try if you're looking for a new sunscreen.

reviews.comments: Sticky and tacky, doesn't layer well under makeup and has white cast

faceoff_positive.comments: I received this item in exchange for my honest opinion and its a Texas summer so this product was definitely needed/necessary. This is a moisturizer that has spf included and is a collagen bank which is an anti-aging item. I will start off by saying that I didn't know this was meant to be a face serum or cream until I looked it up so it would be nice to clarify that for people that are new-ish to skincare products. On to the product, I loved that it feels like a thicker formula aka like a cream and goes on clear thankfully especially when most creams/spf products have a grey cast. This doesn't and it goes on extremely smooth now I can't say for sure how much change I see when it comes to smoothness and care because I have been doing better about skincare lately and my skin already feels fairly smooth and well managed but I will say that this product has no scent and goes on the skin extremely clear and smooth. I had no real issues with it and wouldn't mind purchasing this product again
faceoff_positive.headline: Suns out? screens on.

faceoff_negative.comments:
I received the Neutrogena Collagen Bank Moisturizer with SPF 30 for free from Home Tester Club and Neutrogena in exchange for my honest review.

I've used retinol before but got an allergic reaction so have stayed off of it. I've been looking for an alternative and read that collagen products can be better for sensitive skin so getting to try this has been a good experience. I like that it has SPF 30 included as a duo. So it's easier to remember to apply SPF although it does leave me skin a bit oily. Also directions are a bit confusing as it says to apply SPF but the product has SPF in it so do I need to apply additional SPF? There is a barely noticeable scent which I'd assume is the SPF in it. The pump makes it easy to pour into my palm so I can apply with my 2 fingers in sections. I've had no reactions thus far and am waiting to see if there is any visible results as I've seen no major change.
faceoff_negative.headline: A good collagen based SPF moisturizer
